    <description>Stem segments narrowly obovate, 4–7 × 2–3(–5) cm; areoles 4–6 per diagonal row
        across midstem segment, 8–11 mm apart. Spines in most areoles, of 2 kinds: major spines 1–3
        per areole, only in distal 3–9 areoles, reflexed to porrect, brown, longest 20–40 mm; minor
        spines 5–7 per areole, strongly deflexed, white, 4–7 mm, except middle one to 14 mm. Fruits
        slender; areoles 10–14, bearing 3–6 spines, to 8 mm. 2n = 22.</description>
